# Git Workflow

## Committing Changes

1. Check status: `git status`
2. Add changes: `git add .` (or specific files)
3. Commit: `git commit -m "Brief description"` (commit per file or single commit for minor changes)

## Creating a Pull Request (PR)

1. Ensure changes are committed (see above).
2. Push changes: `git push` (if needed).
3. Check current branch: `git branch`
4. Log branch changes vs main: `git log main..[current branch]`
5. Check file diff vs main: `git diff --name-status main`
6. Create PR using GitHub CLI: `gh pr create --title "Title" --body "Single line body description..."` (Assume CLI is authenticated).